1
00:03:19,017 --> 00:03:20,225
What's it made of?

2
00:03:20,433 --> 00:03:22,392
Bull's horn

3
00:03:22,558 --> 00:03:23,558
I'll take them

4
00:03:23,725 --> 00:03:24,933
Thank you

5
00:03:25,225 --> 00:03:27,475
Buy the small ones for me, Mum?

6
00:03:27,642 --> 00:03:29,183
Of course, my darling

7
00:03:29,350 --> 00:03:30,809
You want them all!

8
00:03:31,017 --> 00:03:33,350
Put them on me, Mum?

9
00:03:39,434 --> 00:03:40,642
You are beautiful!

10
00:03:40,809 --> 00:03:41,767
You like me?

11
00:03:41,934 --> 00:03:43,892
You are ravishing.

12
00:03:44,684 --> 00:03:45,434
Really?

13
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:48,517
Honestly. Hey, careful with the hat!

14
00:03:52,642 --> 00:03:54,767
Buy one?

15
00:03:56,975 --> 00:03:57,725
You like it?

16
00:03:57,934 --> 00:03:59,642
I find it obscene.

17
00:03:59,850 --> 00:04:03,767
Obscene? When one can hear Yemaya,

18
00:04:03,975 --> 00:04:06,225
The goddess of the oceans

19
00:04:18,767 --> 00:04:21,225
You want to buy a hat?

20
00:04:21,475 --> 00:04:22,184
Mum!

21
00:04:22,392 --> 00:04:23,850
Oh, what a pretty blonde!

22
00:04:24,059 --> 00:04:26,017
You play dice?

23
00:04:26,642 --> 00:04:27,892
Play with us!

24
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:32,142
Where's my little girl?

25
00:04:32,350 --> 00:04:34,309
She's having fun over there.

26
00:04:34,517 --> 00:04:35,767
Rebecca!

27
00:04:44,725 --> 00:04:46,184
What happened?

28
00:04:46,392 --> 00:04:47,642
I lost an earring

29
00:04:48,434 --> 00:04:49,600
You are the father?

30
00:04:49,809 --> 00:04:51,059
The
father-in-law.

31
00:04:51,225 --> 00:04:55,059
A pretty girl. Can I buy her from you?

32
00:04:55,892 --> 00:04:58,184
Interesting idea. How much?

33
00:04:58,392 --> 00:04:59,392
A thousand coconuts!

34
00:04:59,725 --> 00:05:01,100
A thousand coconuts?

35
00:05:01,434 --> 00:05:03,225
She is worth much more!

36
00:05:03,392 --> 00:05:08,600
Look at this hair, these eyes,
these teeth. She is healthy.

37
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:10,975
And wild like you

38
00:05:11,350 --> 00:05:13,225
A thousand coconuts

39
00:05:13,850 --> 00:05:15,392
Fifteen hundred

40
00:05:17,184 --> 00:05:19,642
- Two thousand coconuts minimum
- don't play the fool!

41
00:05:19,809 --> 00:05:22,892
Two thousand coconuts minimum

42
00:05:25,017 --> 00:05:26,434
Who'll give them?

43
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:30,767
She's gone! You always torment her!

44
00:06:18,517 --> 00:06:21,184
B. del Pramo, who does
not sing any more..

45
00:06:21,350 --> 00:06:24,725
since her 2nd marriage to Mr. Ocana...

46
00:06:24,892 --> 00:06:27,809
has had an interesting offer of...

47
00:06:27,975 --> 00:06:29,975
a role in Mexico.

48
00:06:30,225 --> 00:06:32,934
To work? You have the house

49
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:36,434
and your daughter to
look after she needs it..

50
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,559
Don't involve Rebecca in this...

51
00:06:38,725 --> 00:06:41,434
I am an artist, not a housewife!

52
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,934
I did not have to get married

53
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:47,559
I am not the only married actress

54
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,892
We'll talk about it on my return

55
00:06:51,059 --> 00:06:55,100
I do not want to argue,
I'm going to accept

56
00:06:55,267 --> 00:06:56,267
No chance

57
00:06:56,434 --> 00:06:57,267
What?

58
00:06:57,475 --> 00:07:01,475
As long as you are my wife,
you will remain here...

59
00:07:01,642 --> 00:07:02,309
me...

60
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:05,142
I am not modern like your ex-husband.

61
00:07:05,309 --> 00:07:07,267
That, I know.

62
00:07:11,642 --> 00:07:13,642
Valium...

63
00:07:14,184 --> 00:07:16,100
Ponderil...

64
00:07:23,184 --> 00:07:24,642
Rebecca, are you in there?

65
00:07:24,809 --> 00:07:26,934
Yes, I'm here

66
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:29,017
Are you insane?

67
00:07:29,184 --> 00:07:32,017
No need to be rude, I'm going

68
00:07:39,017 --> 00:07:43,100
I'll say it again, it is my bathroom

69
00:07:43,850 --> 00:07:45,975
And mother's

70
00:07:49,559 --> 00:07:50,850
Are you off?

71
00:07:51,017 --> 00:07:52,100
Yes

72
00:07:52,309 --> 00:07:55,267
On my return, we will discuss...

73
00:07:55,434 --> 00:07:57,559
evesdropping

74
00:07:57,725 --> 00:07:59,184
OK

75
00:07:59,767 --> 00:08:00,892
Ok mum?

76
00:08:01,475 --> 00:08:04,142
M. Ocana was buried...

77
00:08:04,309 --> 00:08:05,100
this morning...

78
00:08:05,267 --> 00:08:07,225
What a family!

79
00:08:07,392 --> 00:08:09,350
Dad must be happy

80
00:08:09,517 --> 00:08:10,767
Why?

81
00:08:11,475 --> 00:08:14,142
He did not love Alberto either

82
00:08:14,309 --> 00:08:16,350
The very idea!

83
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:21,600
After the crash, Mr.
Ocana's car caught fire.

84
00:08:21,767 --> 00:08:25,017
The driver fell asleep...

85
00:08:25,184 --> 00:08:30,184
the car left the road and struck a tree

86
00:08:30,850 --> 00:08:34,975
The health of the Prime
Minister is excellent and...

87
00:08:35,434 --> 00:08:37,850
Why go to Mexico?

88
00:08:38,017 --> 00:08:42,975
To work, it is most important now

89
00:08:43,142 --> 00:08:44,559
And the photographs?

90
00:08:44,725 --> 00:08:48,434
Let us speak about
filming, not photographs

91
00:08:48,892 --> 00:08:51,225
My husband has just died

92
00:08:51,392 --> 00:08:54,975
I cannot sell these things. Sorry

93
00:08:55,350 --> 00:08:57,309
And if I went to Mexico.

94
00:08:57,684 --> 00:09:01,309
to make a report on filming?

95
00:09:01,475 --> 00:09:03,934
I do not see a problem

96
00:09:06,142 --> 00:09:08,142
You could join me there

97
00:09:08,350 --> 00:09:10,600
Right, fine

98
00:09:12,017 --> 00:09:16,142
If it's an exclusive,
my newspaper will send me

99
00:09:16,309 --> 00:09:17,142
It is

100
00:09:17,309 --> 00:09:18,850
See you in Mexico?

101
00:09:22,725 --> 00:09:26,309
Dad says you're going
without me, you promised

102
00:09:27,017 --> 00:09:28,184
Impossible, darling

103
00:09:28,350 --> 00:09:29,350
Why?

104
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,434
Because...

105
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:33,600
Children do not travel so well

106
00:09:33,767 --> 00:09:35,934
It is necessary to study too

107
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:38,975
There are schools in Mexico

108
00:09:39,142 --> 00:09:40,184
Right, listen.

109
00:09:40,767 --> 00:09:41,725
You're confusing me!

110
00:09:41,892 --> 00:09:42,934
Sorry, treasure

111
00:09:43,225 --> 00:09:48,142
Let's agree that I go to make
a beautiful film in Mexico.

112
00:09:48,309 --> 00:09:51,809
and afterwards, we'll be
together always, promise

113
00:09:51,975 --> 00:09:53,267
I do not believe you!

114
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:56,309
Do not promise the impossible

115
00:09:56,475 --> 00:09:58,767
That's it! Deal with it!

116
00:09:58,975 --> 00:10:00,892
But you promised

117
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:06,059
Yes, dear...if Mum doesn't
go, she will be miserable

118
00:10:06,225 --> 00:10:08,017
You don't want that?

119
00:10:10,017 --> 00:10:13,225
Good, leave us, I must speak to Papa

120
00:10:13,392 --> 00:10:15,350
What will I do with her!

121
00:10:15,517 --> 00:10:17,642
You've done enough, leave it to me

122
00:10:31,434 --> 00:10:34,184
Margarita, the guitar!

123
00:10:35,101 --> 00:10:35,851
Pardon...

124
00:10:36,059 --> 00:10:37,017
Mother

125
00:10:37,226 --> 00:10:39,184
It is me, Rebecca...

126
00:10:51,017 --> 00:10:53,101
Let me look at you

127
00:10:54,642 --> 00:10:56,434
You've become a woman!

128
00:10:56,601 --> 00:10:58,476
Mum, I'm 27

129
00:10:58,684 --> 00:11:03,059
I know, Chanel suits you

130
00:11:03,226 --> 00:11:06,642
It is you who is... ravishing

131
00:11:06,851 --> 00:11:10,434
Wait until I have
rested. And your husband?

132
00:11:10,642 --> 00:11:11,601
He had to go

133
00:11:13,434 --> 00:11:14,309
You will see him

134
00:11:14,517 --> 00:11:18,517
This dumpling who hustled
you, is Margarita, my secretary

135
00:11:19,434 --> 00:11:22,767
Delighted. Your mother's
told me lots about you

136
00:11:22,976 --> 00:11:24,517
- Has she?
- Of course

137
00:11:24,934 --> 00:11:30,267
She is a Catalan, daughter of the
famous Dr. Forner, exiled during the war

138
00:11:30,517 --> 00:11:33,601
And my guardian angel for 10 years

139
00:11:33,767 --> 00:11:35,642
What luck!

140
00:11:35,934 --> 00:11:39,934
I'm missing 2 bags, I
leave you the caddie...

141
00:11:42,267 --> 00:11:43,517
Come on, let's get away from the crowd

142
00:11:43,726 --> 00:11:47,559
That's me: always in a crowd!

143
00:11:49,684 --> 00:11:52,517
There's a lot of journalists outside?

144
00:11:52,684 --> 00:11:56,809
Not one, I did not
reveal your date of return

145
00:11:57,184 --> 00:11:59,017
Why? I don't have scabies!

146
00:11:59,851 --> 00:12:01,892
I wanted to avoid the scuffle

147
00:12:02,809 --> 00:12:06,684
It's just
- I'm back after so many years!

148
00:12:06,851 --> 00:12:09,726
I don't often wear this hat!

149
00:12:10,059 --> 00:12:11,684
I expected more interest

150
00:12:12,601 --> 00:12:14,434
I awaited you with much interest

151
00:12:15,517 --> 00:12:17,892
That's true darling, forgive me!

152
00:12:18,476 --> 00:12:20,142
It is the time-lag!

153
00:12:30,851 --> 00:12:32,351
Hotel Miguel Angel...

154
00:12:32,517 --> 00:12:33,684
Not our place?

155
00:12:33,851 --> 00:12:38,934
No, I am independent, and
I do not want to disturb you

156
00:12:39,226 --> 00:12:41,392
But we'll see a lot of each other?

157
00:12:41,559 --> 00:12:43,726
Of course!

158
00:12:44,476 --> 00:12:47,017
My God, how it's changed!

159
00:12:47,184 --> 00:12:48,892
You will not recognize...

160
00:12:49,059 --> 00:12:53,309
It doesn't matter, as long
as the city recognizes me

161
00:12:53,892 --> 00:12:56,434
Marga, do not take notes

162
00:13:00,351 --> 00:13:01,934
Why was she writing?

163
00:13:02,142 --> 00:13:05,517
Apart from everything else,
she's writing my autobiography.

164
00:13:06,684 --> 00:13:07,892
Am I in it?

165
00:13:08,059 --> 00:13:12,101
Of course, you are my little girl! Why?

166
00:13:12,267 --> 00:13:15,434
I do not like my life read about

167
00:13:16,017 --> 00:13:17,809
Is Manuel in it too?

168
00:13:19,517 --> 00:13:21,142
Let's talk about... Manuel

169
00:13:23,476 --> 00:13:24,976
You married him

170
00:13:25,601 --> 00:13:27,559
and I heard about it by chance

171
00:13:27,726 --> 00:13:29,017
Let us forget that...

172
00:13:31,142 --> 00:13:32,101
You did not tell me

173
00:13:32,559 --> 00:13:35,934
I spoke to you about my
marriage on the telephone

174
00:13:36,517 --> 00:13:38,351
Yes, but not with Manuel

175
00:13:38,934 --> 00:13:40,601
I could not!

176
00:13:40,851 --> 00:13:43,851
You told me you were very busy and...

177
00:13:44,017 --> 00:13:45,392
had no time...

178
00:13:47,476 --> 00:13:50,184
I didn't tell you any lies

179
00:13:52,142 --> 00:13:53,642
True, but...

180
00:13:53,976 --> 00:13:55,559
you should have told me

181
00:13:56,892 --> 00:13:57,684
Still!

182
00:14:00,601 --> 00:14:04,684
You can take us along Alamillo Place?

183
00:14:25,642 --> 00:14:27,851
Oh, a turd. It is nothing.

184
00:14:28,017 --> 00:14:29,142
Through the windows...

185
00:14:30,267 --> 00:14:32,809
one could see people's feet

186
00:14:32,976 --> 00:14:35,767
Sometimes that frightened me

187
00:14:36,267 --> 00:14:39,934
I was 5 years old, you
had not been born of course

188
00:14:40,642 --> 00:14:42,809
I bought it, you know?

189
00:14:43,101 --> 00:14:45,642
You thinking of staying in Madrid?

190
00:14:45,809 --> 00:14:48,642
Yes, I will move as soon as possible

191
00:14:48,809 --> 00:14:52,101
Becky, look, it is you!

192
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:53,559
What did she say?

193
00:14:58,642 --> 00:15:01,726
It hardly looks like
me, the photograph here!

194
00:15:01,892 --> 00:15:06,059
I have one with the
same feathers, same pose

195
00:15:06,267 --> 00:15:09,226
"Letal Woman": the true
Becky. Aren't I the true Becky?

196
00:15:09,392 --> 00:15:10,559
Of course!

197
00:15:10,726 --> 00:15:13,392
That's an imposter who imitates you

198
00:15:13,559 --> 00:15:16,101
And you thought you were forgotten

199
00:15:16,267 --> 00:15:17,142
You've seen him?

200
00:15:17,309 --> 00:15:22,726
Yes, he's a friend... if I
missed you, I was going to see him

201
00:15:23,226 --> 00:15:25,059
I'll await you over there

202
00:15:25,226 --> 00:15:27,392
Forgive my absence

203
00:15:27,892 --> 00:15:30,642
I do not have an excuse, but...

204
00:15:30,809 --> 00:15:33,351
your father did not help...

205
00:15:33,976 --> 00:15:36,642
I know, Mum, quite the contrary

206
00:15:38,309 --> 00:15:39,309
You...

207
00:15:40,392 --> 00:15:42,101
like me still a little bit?

208
00:15:44,559 --> 00:15:46,142
I love you very much

209
00:15:47,851 --> 00:15:49,809
I was afraid that you'd hate me

210
00:15:50,351 --> 00:15:51,559
I did hate you...

211
00:15:52,726 --> 00:15:53,934
but even then...

212
00:15:54,101 --> 00:15:55,809
I still loved you

213
00:16:06,434 --> 00:16:09,226
Ah, I've caught my earring

214
00:16:10,351 --> 00:16:11,851
At last!

215
00:16:19,517 --> 00:16:20,767
You will not believe me!

216
00:16:20,934 --> 00:16:24,601
I had earrings like those

217
00:16:24,767 --> 00:16:28,059
Alberto was alive. I
bought them on an island.

218
00:16:28,809 --> 00:16:30,476
Margarita Island.

219
00:16:30,642 --> 00:16:31,851
You knew?

220
00:16:32,017 --> 00:16:36,059
You bought me these
earrings there the same day

221
00:16:36,267 --> 00:16:40,267
Oh, but of course, what a head I have!

222
00:16:40,434 --> 00:16:42,642
Mum, stop your acting

223
00:16:42,976 --> 00:16:46,726
if not you'll constantly
drop clangers...

224
00:16:46,892 --> 00:16:50,142
The important thing is, we're together

225
00:16:50,351 --> 00:16:52,184
You are right, darling

226
00:16:53,267 --> 00:16:55,059
How grown-up!

227
00:16:59,184 --> 00:17:02,517
I am happy, Rebecca is marvellous

228
00:17:02,726 --> 00:17:04,309
I am relieved

229
00:17:04,517 --> 00:17:07,267
Wait, it's still the
hardest thing for you

230
00:17:07,726 --> 00:17:09,184
Let me come

231
00:17:09,642 --> 00:17:13,559
I'll go alone. It's 15
years since I saw them

232
00:17:13,767 --> 00:17:14,476
Don't be...

233
00:17:14,684 --> 00:17:16,559
a martyr, Becky

234
00:17:17,559 --> 00:17:20,142
I'll try to be kind to her

235
00:17:21,892 --> 00:17:22,809
Look...

236
00:17:23,392 --> 00:17:24,851
She is presenting the news

237
00:17:25,017 --> 00:17:25,851
Let me see...

238
00:17:28,142 --> 00:17:29,309
2 attacks...

239
00:17:29,518 --> 00:17:33,393
were perpetrated this morning by ETA

240
00:17:33,601 --> 00:17:37,809
The 1st led to the death
of Roberto Agalburu...

241
00:17:39,518 --> 00:17:42,518
when a bomb exploded..

242
00:17:42,726 --> 00:17:44,018
under its car

243
00:17:45,393 --> 00:17:48,976
He was a travelling garlic salesman

244
00:17:49,893 --> 00:17:51,268
He was thought to be involved..

245
00:17:51,893 --> 00:17:54,559
with drug trafficking

246
00:17:54,726 --> 00:17:57,476
The attack could have been terrible...

247
00:17:58,393 --> 00:18:00,601
How can she laugh?

248
00:18:01,059 --> 00:18:03,601
...as nearby a creche...

249
00:18:03,976 --> 00:18:05,601
Why am I watching this?

250
00:18:06,393 --> 00:18:07,851
What can I say this evening?

251
00:18:29,518 --> 00:18:30,768
You can go, Lola

252
00:18:30,976 --> 00:18:32,059
It's lovely!

253
00:18:32,476 --> 00:18:35,184
Hang on, you saw the news?

254
00:18:35,351 --> 00:18:37,059
Sorry, I forgot

255
00:18:37,226 --> 00:18:42,268
Too bad... I messed it all up
thinking you were looking...

256
00:18:57,059 --> 00:18:58,726
Hi, Manuel?

257
00:19:00,768 --> 00:19:02,434
Beautiful, isn't she?

258
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:05,726
She's fantastic

259
00:19:11,393 --> 00:19:13,726
Excuse me one moment.

260
00:19:16,601 --> 00:19:20,726
You're happy directing a TV show?

261
00:19:20,934 --> 00:19:23,268
I can't complain

262
00:19:23,643 --> 00:19:26,976
I knew you'd do well

263
00:19:32,101 --> 00:19:34,518
Why didn't you tell
me you'd married her?

264
00:19:34,684 --> 00:19:37,018
She didn't tell me she was your daughter

265
00:19:37,184 --> 00:19:41,018
And you never asked
her about her family?

266
00:19:41,184 --> 00:19:46,268
She told me her father
had died 2 years ago

267
00:19:46,518 --> 00:19:47,309
And her mother?

268
00:19:47,934 --> 00:19:51,184
That she might as well be, since she...

269
00:19:51,351 --> 00:19:53,809
lived abroad

270
00:19:53,976 --> 00:19:56,184
You've no excuses

271
00:19:56,351 --> 00:19:57,601
You less than she

272
00:19:58,934 --> 00:20:02,851
But I am not on the
warpath... on the contrary

273
00:20:03,018 --> 00:20:05,559
I want to find my daughter,
to try to make her happy

274
00:20:06,518 --> 00:20:09,351
But that depends on both of us

275
00:20:09,851 --> 00:20:10,934
You love her don't you?

276
00:20:13,476 --> 00:20:14,559
Listen...

277
00:20:15,059 --> 00:20:15,934
Why?

278
00:20:16,684 --> 00:20:17,893
She adores you

279
00:20:18,309 --> 00:20:19,559
She is difficult

280
00:20:19,934 --> 00:20:21,351
Don't I know it!

